Wash and dry produce. Halve, core, and thinly slice @green bell pepper{1} into strips.

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tbsp}, @cream cheese{4%tbsp}, 1 tsp water (2 tsp for 4 servings), and @hot sauce{2%tsp} to taste. (Start with half the hot sauce, then taste and add more from there if you like things spicy.) Microwave until softened, ~{30%seconds}. Stir to combine.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{}, over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @ground beef{10%oz} to pan with bell pepper. Season with a big pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until beef is browned and cooked through and bell pepper is tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Carefully drain any excess grease in pan.

Stir in @beef stock concentrate{1} until combined. Turn off heat.

Place @flour tortillas{2} on a clean work surface.

Spread one half of each tortilla with half the cream sauce (save the rest for serving). Using a #slotted spoon{}, top cream sauce with beef filling, then sprinkle with @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup}. Fold tortillas in half to create tortilla melts.

Wipe out pan used for filling. Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in same pan over medium heat.

Add tortilla melts (work in batches for 4); cook until tortillas are golden brown and cheese melts, ~{3-4%minutes} per side.

Transfer to a #paper-towel-lined cutting board{}.

Cut tortilla melts into wedges.

Divide between plates and serve with remaining cream sauce on top or on the side for dipping.